1
00:00:09,635 --> 00:00:11,762
If there really is a
giant monster out there,

2
00:00:11,762 --> 00:00:14,056
do you think they'll
authorize us to attack?

3
00:00:14,056 --> 00:00:16,433
If this was a monster
movie, I guarantee

4
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:18,977
we'd be the first
to get killed off.

5
00:00:18,977 --> 00:00:20,938
You know, curtain
raisers to set things up

6
00:00:20,938 --> 00:00:22,731
till the main
character shows up.

7
00:00:22,731 --> 00:00:24,816
Uh, that's not even funny, sir.

8
00:00:24,816 --> 00:00:27,277
Whatever it is, we'll
find out soon enough.

9
00:00:27,277 --> 00:00:30,989
(engines whirring)

10
00:00:32,616 --> 00:00:36,328
(explosive noises)

11
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:41,291
(screaming)

12
00:00:41,291 --> 00:00:45,003
(rumbling)

13
00:00:51,343 --> 00:00:54,012
(thunder rumbling)

14
00:00:54,012 --> 00:00:57,683
(yelling)

15
00:01:04,147 --> 00:01:08,277
Didn't work, it's
just restoring itself.

16
00:01:08,277 --> 00:01:10,529
What incredible
regenerating power.

17
00:01:10,529 --> 00:01:14,533
It's all they can do to
keep it from coming ashore.

18
00:01:14,533 --> 00:01:16,243
Well, at this rate,

19
00:01:16,243 --> 00:01:18,620
I'll never get
through to Caster.

20
00:01:18,620 --> 00:01:20,539
♪

21
00:01:20,539 --> 00:01:23,166
Awesome, so awesome.

22
00:01:23,166 --> 00:01:27,879
That is so totally
awesome, big guy!

23
00:01:27,879 --> 00:01:29,590
The Lord has come.

24
00:01:29,590 --> 00:01:33,385
The Lord has come!

25
00:01:33,385 --> 00:03:02,432
♪

26
00:03:05,394 --> 00:03:09,272
It's terrible, how could
this have happened?

27
00:03:09,272 --> 00:03:12,651
In the long and winding
history of the Holy Grail Wars,

28
00:03:12,651 --> 00:03:15,987
a foul up like this
is unprecedented.

29
00:03:15,987 --> 00:03:18,490
According to our
observers' reports,

30
00:03:18,490 --> 00:03:21,868
even though the Mion River
area is blanketed in mist,

31
00:03:21,868 --> 00:03:26,623
a large number of onlookers have
already begun to gather there.

32
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:30,252
I fear we can no longer
handle this by ourselves.

33
00:03:30,252 --> 00:03:34,965
We must petition the Mage's
Association for assistance.

34
00:03:34,965 --> 00:03:38,635
(sighing)

35
00:03:38,635 --> 00:03:41,304
What is Tokiomi doing right now?

36
00:03:41,304 --> 00:03:43,682
My master left for
the scene with Archer

37
00:03:43,682 --> 00:03:47,602
immediately after
Caster's monster appeared.

38
00:03:47,602 --> 00:03:52,190
In that case, I will see to the
arrangements for the cover up.

39
00:03:52,190 --> 00:03:56,736
Go to Tokiomi immediately and
assist him in any way you can.

40
00:03:56,736 --> 00:03:59,698
I understand, Father.

41
00:03:59,698 --> 00:04:07,664
♪

42
00:04:07,664 --> 00:04:11,793
This sight has begun
to turn my stomach.

43
00:04:11,793 --> 00:04:15,005
Mongrels though they may
be, they are still figures

44
00:04:15,005 --> 00:04:17,716
of at least some slight renown.

45
00:04:17,716 --> 00:04:20,969
Yet here they are working
together with all their might

46
00:04:20,969 --> 00:04:23,722
to finish off that
disgusting thing.

47
00:04:23,722 --> 00:04:28,268
Surely there are limits
to which one may sink.

48
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:31,521
Do you not agree
with that, Tokiomi?

49
00:04:31,521 --> 00:04:33,482
♪

50
00:04:33,482 --> 00:04:35,567
We must destroy that monster

51
00:04:35,567 --> 00:04:39,154
before there are any more
witnesses to the battle.

52
00:04:39,154 --> 00:04:43,116
The honor of the Tohsaka
family is at stake.

53
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:45,827
My king, that
monster is a vermin

54
00:04:45,827 --> 00:04:48,413
that is ravaging your garden.

55
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:52,083
I humbly beseech you
to slay it yourself.

56
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:55,420
Dealing with pests is
the job of a gardener,

57
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:58,673
or is your intent to
mock my Noble Phantasms,

58
00:04:58,673 --> 00:05:02,928
putting them on the level
of a gardener's hoe, Tokiomi.

59
00:05:02,928 --> 00:05:06,097
I would never dream of such
a thing, but as you can see,

60
00:05:06,097 --> 00:05:09,434
Majesty, this creature is beyond
the ability of the others.

61
00:05:09,434 --> 00:05:13,355
It's the perfect opportunity
to demonstrate your true might.

62
00:05:13,355 --> 00:05:16,149
I beg you, please take action.

63
00:05:16,149 --> 00:05:20,612
♪

64
00:05:20,612 --> 00:05:23,782
Hm.

65
00:05:23,782 --> 00:05:27,452
(shouting)

66
00:05:30,539 --> 00:05:34,251
(explosions)

67
00:05:54,646 --> 00:05:57,107
It can't be.

68
00:05:57,107 --> 00:05:58,984
We're leaving, Tokiomi.

69
00:05:58,984 --> 00:06:02,404
I've grown weary of watching
that disgusting creature.

70
00:06:02,404 --> 00:06:06,658
No, King of Heroes,
wait, I beg you.

71
00:06:06,658 --> 00:06:09,578
Tokiomi, I sacrificed
four swords

72
00:06:09,578 --> 00:06:12,789
thinking it might
duty towards you.

73
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:15,959
Having been defiled by
touching that filthy thing,

74
00:06:15,959 --> 00:06:19,045
I have no interest
in retrieving them.

75
00:06:19,045 --> 00:06:21,715
Do not presume
upon my generosity.

76
00:06:21,715 --> 00:06:24,175
You are the only
heroic spirit alive

77
00:06:24,175 --> 00:06:26,344
able to defeat that thing.

78
00:06:26,344 --> 00:06:29,180
Given its regenerative
abilities, the sole way

79
00:06:29,180 --> 00:06:32,100
to defeat it is to
annihilate it in one strike.

80
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:35,103
Only your Sword of
Dissociation is capable

81
00:06:35,103 --> 00:06:38,857
‐of accomplishing that so‐‐
‐You fool!

82
00:06:38,857 --> 00:06:41,860
You dare suggest that
I draw forth Ea here!

83
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:45,447
Don't forget your place,
I should have your head

84
00:06:45,447 --> 00:06:48,533
for being so impertinent
to your king!

85
00:06:52,662 --> 00:06:56,666
I could use a Command Seal,
but if I did, it would shatter

86
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:59,544
my relationship with
the King of Heroes.

87
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:01,713
Father Risei and I had
originally arranged

88
00:07:01,713 --> 00:07:03,882
for this Caster
hunting expedition

89
00:07:03,882 --> 00:07:07,385
so that I could recover
the Command Seal I lost.

90
00:07:07,385 --> 00:07:11,473
How could my plan be
backfiring so badly?

91
00:07:13,642 --> 00:07:16,144
(whooshing noise)

92
00:07:18,229 --> 00:07:19,773
Damn.

93
00:07:19,773 --> 00:07:22,734
♪

94
00:07:22,734 --> 00:07:25,070
What the hell is that?

95
00:07:25,070 --> 00:07:28,823
There's a weird light hovering
in the sky at six o'clock.

96
00:07:28,823 --> 00:07:30,533
It's not a helicopter.

97
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:34,287
Is it a UFO or something?

98
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:36,289
Control to Diablo One,

99
00:07:36,289 --> 00:07:39,459
we need a situation report.

100
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:41,544
The situation is,

101
00:07:41,544 --> 00:07:44,673
uh, well...

102
00:07:44,673 --> 00:07:49,094
Diablo Two, gonna go down
to get a closer look.

103
00:07:49,094 --> 00:07:51,596
Wait, Kobayashi!

104
00:07:51,596 --> 00:07:55,350
Diablo Two, get back here!

105
00:07:55,350 --> 00:07:57,143
Official inspection
from up close

106
00:07:57,143 --> 00:07:59,062
will tell us what that thing is.

107
00:07:59,062 --> 00:08:01,064
(screaming)

108
00:08:01,064 --> 00:08:02,899
Kobayashi.

109
00:08:02,899 --> 00:08:19,916
♪

110
00:08:19,916 --> 00:08:22,168
Kobayashi!

111
00:08:22,168 --> 00:08:26,381
♪

112
00:08:26,381 --> 00:08:29,259
A fearsome creature indeed.

113
00:08:29,259 --> 00:08:31,886
It‐‐it ate it.

114
00:08:31,886 --> 00:08:34,931
(evil laughter)

115
00:08:34,931 --> 00:08:38,643
♪

116
00:08:38,643 --> 00:08:40,687
Control to Diablo One.

117
00:08:40,687 --> 00:08:42,856
What's going on over there?

118
00:08:42,856 --> 00:08:44,858
Report!

119
00:08:44,858 --> 00:08:47,485
Eyes, it has eyes.

120
00:08:47,485 --> 00:08:50,989
It's absolutely
covered with eyes!

121
00:08:50,989 --> 00:08:54,242
Eyes, what do you
mean it has eyes?

122
00:08:54,242 --> 00:08:58,288
Shit, that thing
wants to eat me too.

123
00:08:58,288 --> 00:09:00,623
Captain Ogi.

124
00:09:00,623 --> 00:09:03,001
Diablo One engaging.

125
00:09:03,001 --> 00:09:05,837
Wait, Ogi, engaging what?

126
00:09:05,837 --> 00:09:08,882
I'll kill it before it gets me.

127
00:09:08,882 --> 00:09:11,301
This is for Kobayashi.

128
00:09:11,301 --> 00:09:13,887
I'm gonna pump you with
missiles, ya bastard.

129
00:09:13,887 --> 00:09:19,809
♪

130
00:09:19,809 --> 00:09:23,146
‐Berserker?
‐Oh man, what's he doing here?

131
00:09:23,146 --> 00:09:26,399
You fool, stay down!

132
00:09:26,399 --> 00:09:29,444
Now he decides to join us?

133
00:09:29,444 --> 00:09:32,363
(growling)

134
00:09:32,363 --> 00:09:37,410
♪

135
00:09:37,410 --> 00:09:40,288
Isn't that...

136
00:09:40,288 --> 00:09:44,042
Ah, so that mad dog
has turned up again.

137
00:09:44,042 --> 00:09:45,794
This should be amusing.

138
00:09:45,794 --> 00:09:48,421
(shouting)

139
00:09:48,421 --> 00:09:52,175
My king, allow me to
deal with his master.

140
00:09:52,175 --> 00:09:55,470
Very well, merely toy with him.

141
00:09:55,470 --> 00:09:58,139
Then good luck to us
both, Your Majesty.

142
00:09:58,139 --> 00:10:02,811
♪

143
00:10:10,568 --> 00:10:13,696
(whooshing noise)

144
00:10:13,696 --> 00:10:16,449
♪

145
00:10:16,449 --> 00:10:20,411
Dogs like you belong
prostrated on the ground.

146
00:10:20,411 --> 00:10:24,249
Yet you dare to
climb into my sky.

147
00:10:24,249 --> 00:10:27,752
Don't put on airs, you mongrel!

148
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:44,144
♪

149
00:10:44,144 --> 00:10:46,229
Such impertinence.

150
00:10:46,229 --> 00:11:14,883
♪

151
00:11:14,883 --> 00:11:16,342
How amusing.

152
00:11:16,342 --> 00:11:19,721
I've not played a game like
this in quite some time.

153
00:11:19,721 --> 00:11:22,348
For a lowly animal,
you're providing me

154
00:11:22,348 --> 00:11:24,851
with no shortage
of entertainment.

155
00:11:24,851 --> 00:11:28,188
♪

156
00:11:28,188 --> 00:11:31,191
(breathing unevenly)

157
00:11:32,275 --> 00:11:34,944
I hardly recognize you,

158
00:11:34,944 --> 00:11:38,823
Kariya Matou.

159
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:41,159
Though you turned your
back on magecraft,

160
00:11:41,159 --> 00:11:43,703
you still desired the Grail.

161
00:11:43,703 --> 00:11:47,248
To think you'd slink back
in such a sorry state.

162
00:11:47,248 --> 00:11:50,335
The very sight of you is
enough to invite whispers

163
00:11:50,335 --> 00:11:54,088
that the Matou family
has fallen from grace.

164
00:11:54,088 --> 00:11:56,424
(laughing)

165
00:11:56,424 --> 00:12:00,053
Tokiomi Tohsaka,
answer me a question.

166
00:12:00,053 --> 00:12:04,515
Why did you hand your daughter
Sakura over to Zouken?

167
00:12:04,515 --> 00:12:07,227
What, you really
think that's what

168
00:12:07,227 --> 00:12:09,395
you should be worrying
about at this moment?

169
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:13,858
Answer me, Tokiomi!

170
00:12:13,858 --> 00:12:16,486
Do you even need to ask?

171
00:12:16,486 --> 00:12:18,029
I did it because
I wished to give

172
00:12:18,029 --> 00:12:21,449
my beloved daughter
a happy future.

173
00:12:21,449 --> 00:12:23,618
You what?

174
00:12:23,618 --> 00:12:27,622
All mages who have two children
eventually suffer for it.

175
00:12:27,622 --> 00:12:31,876
The family's secret arts can
be passed to only one child.

176
00:12:31,876 --> 00:12:34,545
They suffer over the
issue that one of them

177
00:12:34,545 --> 00:12:38,424
must be cast down
into the common masses.

178
00:12:38,424 --> 00:12:42,387
The simple fact is that my wife
is superior breeding stock.

179
00:12:42,387 --> 00:12:45,723
Both Rin and Sakura were
born with equally rare

180
00:12:45,723 --> 00:12:49,102
natural gifts and
magical abilities.

181
00:12:49,102 --> 00:12:52,480
And so both my daughters
were in need of the protection

182
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:55,733
and nurturing attention
of a mage family.

183
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:58,486
For the future of one
daughter I must waste

184
00:12:58,486 --> 00:13:02,657
the vast potential lurking
deep inside the other?

185
00:13:02,657 --> 00:13:05,410
What father would wish
such a woeful tragedy

186
00:13:05,410 --> 00:13:09,414
upon his children?

187
00:13:09,414 --> 00:13:11,749
Common masses.

188
00:13:11,749 --> 00:13:15,920
The memory of his children
and their mother on that day.

189
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:17,922
This heartless man
is writing it off

190
00:13:17,922 --> 00:13:21,259
as something for
the common masses.

191
00:13:21,259 --> 00:13:25,054
If I was to preserve the hopes I
had for both sisters' abilities,

192
00:13:25,054 --> 00:13:28,641
my only option would
be to send one away.

193
00:13:28,641 --> 00:13:33,354
That is why the Matou family's
offer was such a godsend.

194
00:13:33,354 --> 00:13:36,316
If she were to be adopted
by a mage family,

195
00:13:36,316 --> 00:13:38,443
it would give her that
much greater chance

196
00:13:38,443 --> 00:13:40,862
of reaching the root.

197
00:13:40,862 --> 00:13:44,407
A mage is someone who
is born with great power,

198
00:13:44,407 --> 00:13:46,451
and before he knows
it, he will attain

199
00:13:46,451 --> 00:13:49,871
even greater heights of power.

200
00:13:49,871 --> 00:13:52,665
Even before a mage
embraces his destiny,

201
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:56,169
his responsibility to
do so is in his blood.

202
00:13:56,169 --> 00:13:59,839
That is what it means to be
born the child of a mage.

203
00:13:59,839 --> 00:14:01,716
♪

204
00:14:01,716 --> 00:14:05,303
If I fail, it falls
to my daughter, Rin,

205
00:14:05,303 --> 00:14:09,098
and even if Rin fails
in her quest, then Sakura

206
00:14:09,098 --> 00:14:12,727
may yet fulfill the dream
of the Tohsaka family.

207
00:14:12,727 --> 00:14:15,521
♪

208
00:14:15,521 --> 00:14:19,484
You bastard, you want
them to fight each other?

209
00:14:19,484 --> 00:14:21,527
Sister against sister?

210
00:14:21,527 --> 00:14:24,614
Even if such a development
were to come to pass,

211
00:14:24,614 --> 00:14:27,950
it is still best for the
future of my descendents.

212
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:29,410
What?

213
00:14:29,410 --> 00:14:31,287
Glory will go to the victor,

214
00:14:31,287 --> 00:14:34,749
and to the loser, honor to
the family of her forbearers.

215
00:14:34,749 --> 00:14:37,585
The best outcome I could
possibly hope for.

216
00:14:37,585 --> 00:14:40,963
You bastard, you're insane!

217
00:14:40,963 --> 00:14:44,675
It is a waste of time to
try to explain it to you.

218
00:14:44,675 --> 00:14:47,595
You don't comprehend
magecraft's grandeur,

219
00:14:47,595 --> 00:14:50,473
and even turned your back
and walked away from it.

220
00:14:50,473 --> 00:14:53,643
‐A lowly traitor.
‐Screw you, bastard!

221
00:14:53,643 --> 00:14:57,355
(groaning)

222
00:15:00,441 --> 00:15:03,236
(growling)

223
00:15:03,236 --> 00:15:58,875
♪

224
00:15:58,875 --> 00:16:02,587
(groaning)

225
00:16:02,587 --> 00:16:05,882
I'll make all you bastards pay.

226
00:16:05,882 --> 00:16:09,427
You filthy rotten mages.

227
00:16:09,427 --> 00:16:11,429
I'll kill you all.

228
00:16:11,429 --> 00:16:14,390
Zouken and you.

229
00:16:14,390 --> 00:16:16,517
Every last one of you.

230
00:16:16,517 --> 00:16:19,103
I'll kill you all.

231
00:16:19,103 --> 00:16:22,190
When you turned down
the family leadership,

232
00:16:22,190 --> 00:16:26,402
the Matou's magic secrets
were passed on to Sakura.

233
00:16:26,402 --> 00:16:29,697
In spite of the fact that I
really should be thanking you

234
00:16:29,697 --> 00:16:32,491
for my Sakura's future,

235
00:16:32,491 --> 00:16:35,620
you are one man that
I simply cannot abide.

236
00:16:35,620 --> 00:16:37,622
♪

237
00:16:37,622 --> 00:16:40,958
The weakness revealed by
shirking of your obligations,

238
00:16:40,958 --> 00:16:43,127
the deficient character
revealed by your lack

239
00:16:43,127 --> 00:16:45,171
of indebtedness to it.

240
00:16:45,171 --> 00:16:48,466
You, Kariya Matou,
are a disgrace.

241
00:16:48,466 --> 00:16:51,886
Having crossed paths with
you again I have no choice

242
00:16:51,886 --> 00:16:53,930
but to put you to death.

243
00:16:53,930 --> 00:16:58,142
Don't talk so high and
mighty, you inhuman bastard.

244
00:16:58,142 --> 00:17:01,479
You're mistaken, shouldering
one's responsibilities

245
00:17:01,479 --> 00:17:04,649
is the first requisite
of being human.

246
00:17:04,649 --> 00:17:07,443
It is those who fail to do so...

247
00:17:07,443 --> 00:17:11,322
♪

248
00:17:11,322 --> 00:17:13,741
...that are subhuman dogs.

249
00:17:13,741 --> 00:17:16,369
‐Kariya.
‐Hear me now, bugs.

250
00:17:16,369 --> 00:17:19,664
Devour this bastard.

251
00:17:19,664 --> 00:17:21,749
Eat him alive!

252
00:17:25,253 --> 00:17:27,630
Oh yeah, go get 'em, Bluebeard!

253
00:17:27,630 --> 00:17:30,341
Crush 'em down, tear 'em apart!

254
00:17:30,341 --> 00:17:33,970
This place is God's toy box!

255
00:17:33,970 --> 00:17:35,763
Saber!

256
00:17:35,763 --> 00:17:48,192
♪

257
00:17:48,192 --> 00:17:50,278
I am much obliged, Saber.

258
00:17:50,278 --> 00:17:56,117
♪

259
00:17:56,117 --> 00:17:59,370
(laughing)

260
00:17:59,370 --> 00:18:02,248
I'll never be bored
again as long as I live.

261
00:18:02,248 --> 00:18:05,001
I won't have to go through all
the trouble of murdering people.

262
00:18:05,001 --> 00:18:08,546
They'll die in droves
without me lifting a finger.

263
00:18:08,546 --> 00:18:11,257
They'll be flattened,
chopped to bits,

264
00:18:11,257 --> 00:18:13,551
smashed, eaten.

265
00:18:13,551 --> 00:18:16,637
They'll die and die
and die left and right.

266
00:18:16,637 --> 00:18:20,224
I'll be able to see one kind
of guts and gore after another

267
00:18:20,224 --> 00:18:23,102
that I've never seen before.

268
00:18:23,102 --> 00:18:25,187
All day, every day,

269
00:18:25,187 --> 00:18:28,149
all around the world,
everywhere I look!

270
00:18:28,149 --> 00:18:30,943
It'll be nonstop, never‐end‐‐

271
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:33,529
(gasping)

272
00:18:33,529 --> 00:18:36,407
♪

273
00:18:36,407 --> 00:18:39,368
‐It stopped moving.
‐Hm?

274
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:41,662
(crowd murmuring)

275
00:18:41,662 --> 00:18:45,041
What the‐‐hey, what happened?

276
00:18:45,041 --> 00:18:47,543
(whimpering)

277
00:18:47,543 --> 00:18:49,503
Huh?

278
00:18:49,503 --> 00:18:53,215
(wind blowing)

279
00:18:56,302 --> 00:18:59,055
That's so pretty.

280
00:19:02,350 --> 00:19:04,393
Now I get it.

281
00:19:04,393 --> 00:19:07,813
No wonder I never
realized it before.

282
00:19:07,813 --> 00:19:09,940
Oh man, talk about
not being able

283
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:13,110
to see the forest for the trees.

284
00:19:13,110 --> 00:19:15,029
It was in me.

285
00:19:15,029 --> 00:19:17,948
I was looking for my own guts.

286
00:19:17,948 --> 00:19:21,285
I didn't have to go
searching for it.

287
00:19:21,285 --> 00:19:25,122
It was hiding right
there all along.

288
00:19:25,122 --> 00:19:27,458
Ryuunosuke!

289
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:32,338
I finally found you.

290
00:19:32,338 --> 00:19:37,134
I've been looking
for you my whole life.

291
00:19:37,134 --> 00:19:39,470
What the hell, man?

292
00:19:39,470 --> 00:19:42,139
If you were inside me all along,

293
00:19:42,139 --> 00:19:44,558
I wish you would've

294
00:19:44,558 --> 00:19:48,187
just told me so
in the first place.

295
00:19:51,899 --> 00:19:55,611
(gunshot firing)

296
00:20:06,789 --> 00:20:10,543
Ryuunosuke, my master.

297
00:20:10,543 --> 00:20:14,880
How could you die and
leave me here all alone?

298
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:18,509
But never you fear,
dear Ryuunosuke,

299
00:20:18,509 --> 00:20:21,512
for I, Gilles de
Rais, will fulfill

300
00:20:21,512 --> 00:20:24,223
the solemn promise
I made to you.

301
00:20:24,223 --> 00:20:28,060
♪

302
00:20:28,060 --> 00:20:30,730
Ryuunosuke, watch closely!

303
00:20:30,730 --> 00:20:33,023
Behold my offering to you!

304
00:20:33,023 --> 00:20:36,944
I shall give you the
greatest "cool!" ever!

305
00:20:36,944 --> 00:20:43,284
♪

306
00:20:43,284 --> 00:20:47,538
I just put down the man I
believe to be Caster's master.

307
00:20:47,538 --> 00:20:50,541
It looks like I was
right about him.

308
00:20:50,541 --> 00:20:53,878
While all the other servants are
being distracted by the monster,

309
00:20:53,878 --> 00:20:56,213
shall I eliminate
the next target?

310
00:20:56,213 --> 00:21:00,384
Wait, Maiya, that's
no ordinary monster.

311
00:21:00,384 --> 00:21:03,554
It's a creature with limitless
regenerative ability.

312
00:21:03,554 --> 00:21:05,306
It's still possible
that it could reach

313
00:21:05,306 --> 00:21:07,183
the shore before it dissipates.

314
00:21:07,183 --> 00:21:10,269
If it does and begins
to feed, it's all over.

315
00:21:10,269 --> 00:21:12,146
Caster will have a
new source of mana

316
00:21:12,146 --> 00:21:13,939
to maintain his physical form.

317
00:21:13,939 --> 00:21:16,817
If that happens, the damage
will spread even further,

318
00:21:16,817 --> 00:21:18,778
and there's a risk
that the Holy Grail War

319
00:21:18,778 --> 00:21:20,905
itself will break down.

320
00:21:20,905 --> 00:21:22,907
Exactly.

321
00:21:22,907 --> 00:21:26,243
But how do we kill an
indestructible monster?

322
00:21:26,243 --> 00:21:29,580
The only way is to annihilate
it in a single strike.

323
00:21:29,580 --> 00:21:32,958
To do that, its entire body
will have to be incinerated.

324
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:36,837
Leaving nothing, not even
the smallest scrap of flesh.

325
00:21:36,837 --> 00:21:39,715
Anti‐Personnel Noble
Phantasms won't suffice.

326
00:21:39,715 --> 00:21:43,552
An Anti‐Fortress one is needed.

327
00:21:43,552 --> 00:21:47,765
Saber possesses just such an
Anti‐Fortress Noble Phantasm.

328
00:21:47,765 --> 00:21:50,643
♪

329
00:21:50,643 --> 00:21:53,270
However, because
of Lancer's curse,

330
00:21:53,270 --> 00:21:56,232
she can't use it.

331
00:21:56,232 --> 00:21:58,359
We'll just have to wait and see

332
00:21:58,359 --> 00:22:00,986
exactly what they
can really accomplish

333
00:22:00,986 --> 00:22:04,073
with their so‐called
chivalric spirit.

334
00:22:07,284 --> 00:23:35,581
♪

335
00:23:37,875 --> 00:23:40,502
Oh, this brilliant light!

336
00:23:40,502 --> 00:23:42,838
‐You prolonged the inevitable.
‐The invincible king

337
00:23:42,838 --> 00:23:45,424
is about to cry out the
true name of the miracle.

338
00:23:45,424 --> 00:23:48,469
‐It is too painful to look upon.
‐Is he trying to kill himself?

339
00:23:48,469 --> 00:23:52,264
‐We must stop its advance!
‐I'm counting on you, Saber.

